text.tspan: Female labor force participation rates by family benefits public
The labor force participation rate corresponds to the proportion of the population ages 15 and older that is economically
active. Family benefits spending refer to public spending on financial support for families and children, such as
child-related cash transfers, public spending on services, and tax provisions.

Female labor force participation rate (%)
(% of female population ages 15+ modeled ILO estimate)
Data source: International Labour Organization, ILOSTAT, via World Bank (2025); OECD (2016)
